observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Management:
a.     Exert efforts in the tracing of acquisition of those property presented in the reconciling items in order to establish the cost, existence, ownership and control to those property;

b. Investigate and submit explanation why property that were funded by the LGU were not recognized/presented in the RCPPE;

c.   Require the General Services Office to submit an updated status of property not yet awarded to the LGU for their proper recognition in the accounting books; and

d. Direct the Municipal Accountant to record the necessary adjustments in order to present a fair and reliable balance of the Property, Plant and Equipment in accordance with PPSAS 17.

We recommended that the Management:
Exert efforts in the tracing of acquisition of those properties presented in the reconciling items in order to establish the cost, existence, ownership and control to those properties;
Investigate and submit explanation why properties that were funded by the LGU were not recognized/presented in the RCPPE;
Require the General Services Office to submit an updated status of properties not yet awarded to the LGU for their proper recognition in the accounting books; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to record the necessary adjustments in order to present a fair and reliable balance of the Property, Plant and Equipment in accordance with PPSAS 17.

We recommended that Management:
Create the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality, whether acquired through purchase or donation, including those constructed by administration and found at station; 
Thru the Inventory Committee created, update the property records based on the results of physical inventory and reconcile with accounting records; 

Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and 

After the inventory taking, direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the updated ledger cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to Section 269 of the GAM for LGUs.

We recommended that Management: 

Submit justification on why the subject consultancy service was engaged by the Municipality as it is tantamount to an unnecessary and irregular expenditure in COA Circular No. 2012-003 dated October 29, 2012;
Immediately terminate the contract of service with this consultant; 

Hire consultant/s only for services which require expertise or knowledge that cannot be performed/offered by the present employees of the Municipality to avoid incurrence of unnecessary expenditures; and 

Comply with the pertinent provisions of Republic Act No. 9184 and its Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) in the procurement of consultancy services.

