We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
General Service Officer (GSO) to maintain an updated Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card of all roads within its area of jurisdiction;
Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of the road components for road projects;
Municipal Accountant to record amount of road networks from 2016 and prior years and include in in the Notes to Financial Statements a separate disclosure for “Road Networks” based on the Registry of Public Infrastructure; and
Inventory committee to conduct inventory of local roads, highways and bridges within the municipality’s area of jurisdiction which were acquired thru purchase or construction, and donation or transfer without cost.

We recommended that Management:

submit the irrevocable standby letter of credit/security bond/bank guarantee, if any, was submitted by the contractor;

require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to explain in writing the reason for the failure to recoup the mobilization fee from the progress billings paid to the Contractor;

instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that supporting documents of the disbursement vouchers are complete to prove the validity and legality of the claims and refrain from paying mobilization fee in the absence of the required irrevocable standby letter of credit/security bond/bank guarantee.

